tories of galaxies on their cluster populations, finding that\n(at similar present-day mass) earlier-forming galaxies foster a more massive\nand disruption-resilient cluster population, while galaxies with late mergers\nare capable of forming massive clusters even at late cosmic epochs. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Nov 2017 19:00:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-28"}
